Package com.intellij.xdebugger.frame

Class XValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.xdebugger.frame.XValueContainer
      • com.intellij.xdebugger.frame.XValue
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    XNamedValue

    public abstract class XValue
extends XValueContainer
    Represents a value in debugger tree. Override XValueContainer.computeChildren(com.intellij.xdebugger.frame.XCompositeNode) if value has a properties which should be shown as child nodes

      • computePresentation

        public abstract void computePresentation(XValueNode node,
                                         XValuePlace place)
        Start computing presentation of the value in the debugger tree and call XValueNode.setPresentation(javax.swing.Icon, String, String, boolean) when computation is finished. Note that this method is called from the Event Dispatch thread so it should return quickly.
        Parameters:
        node - node
        place - where the node will be shown.

      • getReferrersProvider

        public XReferrersProvider getReferrersProvider()
